<TITLE> Ministry seeks cabinet advice on ship-breaking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 01 (bdnews24.com)  The shipping ministry has sought cabinet advice for designating a ministry to monitor and execute the required duties to develop the ship breaking industry. It will be sending a letter to the cabinet within two days asking for clarification of the matter. The ministry's public relations officer Jahangir Alam Khan revealed that the decision was taken at an inter-ministerial meeting on Tuesday. The industry's importance as a recycler was highlighted in the meeting saying that it recovers around 20-25 lakh tonnes of iron and 30-35 thousand tonnes of furniture every year. The industry is also responsible for direct and indirect employment of around 500,000 people. It was also highlighted in the meeting that the industry boosts development of several other industries like ship-building. The ministry's acting secretary Abdul Mannan Hawladar, Industries ministry joint secretary Ganendra Nath Biswas and other senior officials of relevant ministries attended the meeting presided over by shipping minister Shajahan Khan. b
